The paper discusses the spectral efficiency of massive MIMO systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The focus is on the uplink, which involves communication between user terminals and base stations, making it relevant to networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also considers joint decoding by multiple base stations, which is a form of cooperation, making it relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI). The use of multiple antennas at the base stations is a key feature of massive MIMO, making it relevant to multimedia systems (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses interference management, which is a topic related to communication and networking (cs.COM).
